headlines.description: — Franz Wagner scored 29 points, Jalen Suggs hit two free throws with 9.8 seconds left and the Orlando Magic beat the Indiana Pacers 94-90 on Wednesday night to remain unbeaten at home.
headlines.shortLinkText: Franz Wagner scores 29 points, Magic beat Pacers 94-90 to improve to 6-0 at home

headlines.description: — Jayson Tatum had 36 points, 10 assists and eight rebounds, Jaylen Brown added 24 points and 12 rebounds and the Boston Celtics beat the Brooklyn Nets 139-114 on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Tatum scores 36 points, the Celtics pour it on in 2nd half to beat the Nets 139-114

events.name: Chicago Bulls at New York Knicks

headlines.description: — Zach LaVine scored 31 points and Colby White had 22, including the winning free throws with three seconds left, as the Chicago Bulls outlasted the New York Knicks 124-123 on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: LaVine scores 31 points, White hits winning free throws and Bulls outlast Knicks 124-123

headlines.description: — Donovan Mitchell scored 11 of his 23 points in the final three minutes of the game and the Cleveland Cavaliers became the sixth team in NBA history to start a season 13-0 with a 114-106 win over the Philadelphia 76ers on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Cavs beats Sixers 114-106 to become 6th NBA team to start a season 13-0

events.name: New Orleans Pelicans at Oklahoma City Thunder

headlines.description: — Jalen Williams scored 31 points, Shai Gilgeous-Alexander added 29 and the Oklahoma City Thunder beat the short-handed New Orleans Pelicans 106-88 on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Thunder beat short-handed Pelicans 106-88 for 2nd straight win without injured forward Chet Holmgren

headlines.description: — Jalen Green had 21 points and Amen Thompson and Tari Eason added 18 each to lead the Houston Rockets to a 111-103 victory over the Los Angeles Clippers on Wednesday night in the opener of a two-game set.
headlines.shortLinkText: Jalen Green scores 21 points in the Rockets' 111-103 victory over the Clippers

headlines.description: — Giannis Antetokounmpo scored 59 points to pace the Milwaukee Bucks to a 127-120 overtime victory over the Detroit Pistons on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Antetokounmpo scores 59 and Bucks beat Pistons 127-120 in overtime

events.name: Washington Wizards at San Antonio Spurs

headlines.description: — Victor Wembanyama had a career-high 50 points and the San Antonio Spurs rolled to a 139-130 victory over the Washington Wizards on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Wembanyama has career-high 50 points and 8 3-pointers to help Spurs top Wizards, 139-130

events.name: Memphis Grizzlies at Los Angeles Lakers

headlines.description: — LeBron James had 35 points, 14 assists and 12 rebounds for his third straight triple-double and the Los Angeles Lakers rallied to beat the Memphis Grizzlies 128-123 on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: LeBron James has third straight triple-double as Lakers rally for 128-123 victory over Grizzlies

events.name: Minnesota Timberwolves at Portland Trail Blazers

headlines.description: — Shaedon Sharpe scored 33 points, Donovan Clingan narrowly missed a triple-double with 17 points, 13 rebounds and eight blocks on Wednesday, and the Portland Trail Blazers beat the Minnesota Timberwolves for the second straight night 106-98.
headlines.shortLinkText: Sharpe and Clingan power the Trail Blazers to a 106-98 victory over the Timberwolves

headlines.description: — De’Aaron Fox had 29 points and 10 assists, Kevin Huerter scored a season-high 22 points and the Sacramento Kings beat the Phoenix Suns 127-101 on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Fox, Kings beat short-handed Suns for 2nd time in 4 days, 127-101
